<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Defs>
  <ScenarioDef ParentName="ScenarioBase">
    <defName>WestTek_ForcedEvolutionSurvivors</defName>
    <label>Forced Evolution Survivors</label>
    <description>A West Tek cell escaped containment with three viable mutie survivors, a crate of refined dosages, and just enough research to begin reproducing the process. One subject is an older first-generation giant. The other two are later-generation super mutants stable enough to build a colony around.</description>
    <scenario>
      <summary>One first-generation super mutant, two second-generation super mutants, and the first FEV protocol.</summary>
      <parts>
        <li Class="ScenPart_ConfigPage_ConfigureStartingPawns_Xenotypes">
          <def>ConfigurePawnsXenotypes</def>
          <pawnChoiceCount>8</pawnChoiceCount>
          <customSummary>Start with one first-generation super mutant and two second-generation super mutants.</customSummary>
          <xenotypeCounts>
            <li>
              <xenotype>WestTek_Xenotype_SuperMutant_2</xenotype>
              <count>1</count>
              <description>first-generation super mutant</description>
              <requiredAtStart>true</requiredAtStart>
              <allowedDevelopmentalStages>Adult</allowedDevelopmentalStages>
            </li>
            <li>
              <xenotype>WestTek_Xenotype_SuperMutant_1</xenotype>
              <count>2</count>
              <description>second-generation super mutant</description>
              <requiredAtStart>true</requiredAtStart>
              <allowedDevelopmentalStages>Adult</allowedDevelopmentalStages>
            </li>
          </xenotypeCounts>
        </li>
        <li Class="ScenPart_PlayerPawnsArriveMethod">
          <def>PlayerPawnsArriveMethod</def>
          <visible>false</visible>
          <method>DropPods</method>
        </li>
        <li Class="ScenPart_GameStartDialog">
          <def>GameStartDialog</def>
          <text>The facility burned long before you escaped it. What remained were ruined vats, sealed notes, and three living proofs that West Tek got further than anyone should have allowed.

Now the old bunker is gone, the handlers are dead, and your little mutie cadre is alone on a rimworld with ten refined dosages and just enough knowledge to restart the work. Whether that becomes a refuge, an army, or another atrocity is up to you.</text>
          <closeSound>GameStartSting</closeSound>
        </li>
        <li Class="ScenPart_StartingResearch">
          <def>StartingResearch</def>
          <project>WestTek_FEV1</project>
        </li>
        <li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
          <def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
          <thingDef>WestTek_RefinedFEVDosage</thingDef>
          <count>10</count>
        </li>
        <li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
          <def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
          <thingDef>MedicineIndustrial</thingDef>
          <count>15</count>
        </li>
        <li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
          <def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
          <thingDef>MealSurvivalPack</thingDef>
          <count>45</count>
        </li>
        <li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
          <def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
          <thingDef>Steel</thingDef>
          <count>300</count>
        </li>
      </parts>
    </scenario>
  </ScenarioDef>
</Defs>